OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FIndia CEO criticised for   
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fpromoting 18-hour workday  
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, An Indian CEO is being criticised on   
OL,6, social media after he suggested that   
OL,7, new recruits at any job should work 18 
OL,8, hours a day for the first four to five 
OL,9, years of their career.                 
OL,11,FShantanu Deshpande, who is the founder 
OL,12,Fof Bombay Shaving Company, asked young 
OL,13,Fworkers to "worship your work" and     
OL,14,Favoid "rona-dhona (cribbing)" in an    
OL,15,Fonline post.Angry reactions on social  
OL,16,Fmedia said he was promoting a "toxic   
OL,17,Fwork culture".India has strong labour  
OL,18,Flaws, but activists have been demanding
OL,19,Fthat officials need to do more to      
OL,20,Fstrictly implement them.               
